uthor":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 14, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"'Uqbah ibn 'Amir reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cThe day of Arafat, the day of sacrifice, and the three following days of al-Tashriq\u00a0are celebrations for the people of Islam. They are days of eating and drinking.\u201d Al-Tirmidhi said, \"The people of knowledge acted\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":33366,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/09\/07\/fasting-9th-10th-muharram\/","url_meta":{"origin":15067,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on &#8216;Ashura: Fasting 9th and 10th of Muharram","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 7, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Abbas reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, ordered fasting on the day of 'Ashura, the tenth of al-Muharram. Imam al-Tirmidhi said, \u201cIt is reported from Ibn Abbas that he said to fast on the ninth and tenth of the month and to do so\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":3738,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/07\/20\/iftar-dates-water\/","url_meta":{"origin":15067,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Iftar: Breaking fast with dates and water","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 20, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Salman ibn 'Amir reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhen one of you breaks his fast, let him break it with dates for they are blessed. If they are not found, let him break it with water for it is pure.\" Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":15083,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/07\/16\/prophet-sawm-monday-thursday\/","url_meta":{"origin":15067,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Siyam: The Prophet loved to fast Monday, Thursday","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 16, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cThe deeds are presented on Monday and Thursday. Thus, I love for\u00a0my deeds to be\u00a0presented while I am fasting.\u201d Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 747 Grade: Hasan (fair) according to Al-Tirmidhi \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0647\u064f\u0631\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0651 \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/15067","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}